From: cyy <cyyever@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] winegstreamer/media-converter: include <pthread.h> for pthread_mutex_t

media-converter.h declares a pthread_mutex_t member but relied on it
being pulled in transitively; that doesn't happen on macOS. Include
<pthread.h> explicitly.
---
diff --git a/dlls/winegstreamer/media-converter/media-converter.h b/dlls/winegstreamer/media-converter/media-converter.h
index d06534e..ccc3271 100644
--- a/dlls/winegstreamer/media-converter/media-converter.h
+++ b/dlls/winegstreamer/media-converter/media-converter.h
@@ -22,6 +22,7 @@
 #define _FILE_OFFSET_BITS 64
 
 #include <string.h>
+#include <pthread.h>
 #include <utime.h>
 #include <stdarg.h>
 #include <stdbool.h>
